{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db02-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1670"},"text":"§ 1670.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Industrial development bonds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db03-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Issuance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The legislature of the government of American Samoa may cause to be issued after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-09-20"},"text":"September 20, 1984","children":[],"tail":", industrial development bonds (within the meaning of section 103(b)(2) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002015"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002015"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of title 26)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db04-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exemption of all bonds from income taxation by State and local governments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db05-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The interest on any bond or other obligation issued by or on behalf of the Government of American Samoa shall be exempt from taxation by the Government of American Samoa and the governments of any of the several States, the District of Columbia, any territory or possession of the United States, and any subdivision thereof.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db06-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exemption applicable only to income taxes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The exemption provided by paragraph (1) shall not apply to gift, estate, inheritance, legacy, succession, or other wealth transfer taxes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db07-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1670/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cross reference","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For exclusion of interest for purposes of Federal income taxation, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s103"},"text":"section 103 of title 26","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcf85db08-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/454/tII/s202"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–454, title II, § 202","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1733"},"text":"98 Stat. 1733","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2095"},"text":"100 Stat. 2095","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/326/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–326, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1270"},"text":"118 Stat. 1270","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcf85db09-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcf85db0a-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcf85db0b-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 103, referred to in subsec. (a), which related to interest on certain governmental obligations was amended generally by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXIII/s1301/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XIII, § 1301(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2602"},"text":"100 Stat. 2602","children":[],"tail":", and as so amended relates to interest on State and local bonds. Section 103(b)(2), which prior to the general amendment defined industrial development bond, relates to the applicability of the interest exclusion to arbitrage bonds."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcf85db0c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/326"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–326","children":[],"tail":" amended heading and text generally, substituting provisions relating to exemption of all bonds from income taxation by State and local governments for provisions relating to exemption from taxation and definition of State."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsecs. (a), (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Internal Revenue Code of 1986” for “Internal Revenue Code of 1954”, which for purposes of codification was translated as “title 26” thus requiring no change in text."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcf85db0d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcf85db0e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/326/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–326, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1270"},"text":"118 Stat. 1270","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/326/s2"},"text":"“This Act [amending this section] shall apply to obligations issued after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 2004","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
